 {"id":"bd-3ub4","title":"Fix frontend setState after unmount in WebSocket callbacks","description":"# Bug: Frontend setState After Unmount in WebSocket Callbacks\n\n## Problem Statement\nThe WebSocket context in `apps/web/src/lib/websocket-context.tsx` has callbacks (onopen, onmessage, onerror, onclose) that call setState without checking if the component is still mounted. This causes React warnings and potential memory leaks.\n\n## Affected Files\n1. `apps/web/src/lib/websocket-context.tsx` (lines 169-244)\n2. `apps/web/src/hooks/useCAAM.ts` (lines 702-819)\n3. Various hooks with async operations\n\n## Current Behavior (BROKEN)\n```typescript\n// websocket-context.tsx lines 169-244\nconst connect = useCallback(() => {\n  const ws = new WebSocket(wsUrl);\n  \n  ws.onopen = () => {\n    attemptRef.current = 0;\n    updateStatus(\"connected\", 0);  // ⚠️ Can run after unmount\n    resubscribeAll();\n    flushQueue();\n  };\n\n  ws.onmessage = (event) => {\n    // ⚠️ Can run after unmount\n    const data = JSON.parse(event.data);\n    // ... setState operations\n  };\n}, [...]);\n```\n\n## Impact\n- **React warnings**: \"Can't perform a React state update on an unmounted component\"\n- **Memory leaks**: Callbacks keep references to old component state\n- **Potential crashes**: In strict mode or with React 18 concurrent features\n\n## Root Cause\nWebSocket callbacks are set up without checking component mount status. When component unmounts, the WebSocket may still be open and receiving messages.\n\n## Proposed Solution\nUse a mounted ref pattern to guard all setState calls:\n\n### Pattern 1: isMounted Ref\n```typescript\nfunction WebSocketProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {\n  const isMountedRef = useRef(true);\n  \n  useEffect(() => {\n    isMountedRef.current = true;\n    return () => {\n      isMountedRef.current = false;\n    };\n  }, []);\n\n  const connect = useCallback(() => {\n    const ws = new WebSocket(wsUrl);\n    \n    ws.onopen = () => {\n      if (!isMountedRef.current) return;  // Guard\n      updateStatus(\"connected\", 0);\n      resubscribeAll();\n    };\n\n    ws.onmessage = (event) => {\n      if (!isMountedRef.current) return;  // Guard\n      // ... safe to call setState\n    };\n  }, [...]);\n}\n```\n\n### Pattern 2: AbortController (Alternative)\n```typescript\nuseEffect(() => {\n  const controller = new AbortController();\n  \n  const ws = new WebSocket(wsUrl);\n  ws.onmessage = (event) => {\n    if (controller.signal.aborted) return;\n    // ... setState\n  };\n\n  return () => {\n    controller.abort();\n    ws.close();\n  };\n}, []);\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files to Update\n\n1. **websocket-context.tsx**:\n   - Add `isMountedRef`\n   - Guard all setState calls in callbacks\n   - Ensure WebSocket is closed on unmount\n\n2. **useCAAM.ts**:\n   - Add `isMountedRef`\n   - Guard async setState after await points\n\n3. **useNotifications.ts**:\n   - Guard interval callbacks\n\n4. **useDashboard.ts**:\n   - Guard `refreshAllWidgets` callback in intervals\n\n5. **useCollabGraph.ts**:\n   - Guard mock mode interval callbacks\n\n### Common Utility\nCreate a hook for this pattern:\n```typescript\n// hooks/useMountedRef.ts\nexport function useMountedRef(): React.MutableRefObject<boolean> {\n  const isMounted = useRef(false);\n  \n  useEffect(() => {\n    isMounted.current = true;\n    return () => { isMounted.current = false; };\n  }, []);\n  \n  return isMounted;\n}\n\n// Usage\nfunction MyComponent() {\n  const isMounted = useMountedRef();\n  \n  const handleAsync = async () => {\n    const result = await fetchSomething();\n    if (!isMounted.current) return;\n    setState(result);\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### WebSocket Cleanup\nEnsure WebSocket is properly closed on unmount:\n```typescript\nuseEffect(() => {\n  return () => {\n    isMountedRef.current = false;\n    if (wsRef.current) {\n      wsRef.current.close();\n      wsRef.current = null;\n    }\n  };\n}, []);\n```\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n### Unit Tests\n1. Test that setState is not called after unmount\n2. Test that WebSocket is closed on unmount\n3. Test that callbacks are no-ops after unmount\n\n### Integration Tests\n1. Mount component, receive WebSocket message, unmount quickly\n2. Verify no React warning\n3. Verify no memory leak (use React DevTools profiler)\n\n### Manual Testing\n1. Open page with WebSocket, navigate away quickly\n2. Check console for \"Can't perform a React state update\" warning\n3. Verify memory doesn't grow with repeated mount/unmount\n\n## Considerations\n- **React 18**: More strict about this issue; fix is essential\n- **Strict Mode**: Double-invokes effects, making this more visible\n- **Performance**: Ref check is cheap, no performance concern\n- **Consistency**: Apply pattern to all async callbacks in codebase\n\n## Definition of Done\n- [ ] useMountedRef hook created\n- [ ] websocket-context.tsx updated\n- [ ] useCAAM.ts updated\n- [ ] useNotifications.ts updated  \n- [ ] useDashboard.ts updated\n- [ ] useCollabGraph.ts updated\n- [ ] No React warnings in console\n- [ ] Unit tests pass\n- [ ] Memory profiling shows no leak","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T23:30:29.924183499Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T23:39:33.290695873Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T23:39:33.290622587Z","close_reason":"Fixed setState after unmount - added useMountedRef hook and guarded all WebSocket callbacks and async operations","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3ub4","depends_on_id":"bd-35hd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T23:30:29.941322441Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
